India’s NTPC Wants Coal Assets in S. Africa, Mining Weekly Says

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-08-11T07:35:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/india-s-ntpc-wants-coal-assets-in-s-africa-mining-weekly-says.html
NTPC Ltd.,  India ’s biggest power
producer, wants to acquire coal assets in  South Africa  and
conclude long-term supply agreements with local miners, Mining
Weekly reported, citing an unnamed NTPC official.  NTPC is considering entering into supply contracts that
would start at levels of 4 million metric tons a year, ramping
up to 16 million tons, Mining Weekly reported without saying
where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
 jmarais@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  